Songwriter, wrapper and singer, Olanrewaju Abdul-Ganiu Fasasi popularly known by his stage name, Sound Sultan, is dead. Announcing his demise on behalf of the family, Dr. Kayode Fasasi said the singer died after a “long battle with Angioimmunoblastic T-cell Lymphoma.” Sound Sultan died on 11 July 2021 at the age of 44 and left behind a wife and three children. Lymphoma is a cancer of the white blood cells which is the fighter cells of the body and forms a huge part of the immune system. Olanrewaju Fasasi, the Nigerian rapper, who is popularly known as Sound Sultan is currently battling with throat cancer in the United States of America, according to SaharaReporters. SaharaReporters gathered that the artist has commenced chemotherapy in one of the hospitals in the country. Chemotherapy is an aggressive form of chemical… In "Entertainment" Popular Nigerian musician, Sound Sultan has revealed how he felt when he was reunited with a 'student' from the his debut video.  Reunions are meant for catching up on events that happened in the time of separation, and although the pictures painted by black American movies often suggest that it… In "Entertainment" Ace musician Tuface Idibia is in London to star in an Afrobeat live show taking place Saturday 3 May (today) at Kentish Town. There will be other supporting artistes: Sound Sultan, Vice Squad, May7even, Ada Snoop and Chaynelle.The show is the brainchild of Now Musik, Hypertek Digital and ABM. Tickets… In "Style"